(ENGINE SHUTS OFF)

01:54.688 --> 01:57.475
- What's that?
- It's a hole.

01:57.864 --> 01:59.107
Is it supposed to be there?

01:59.109 --> 02:02.414
No. Most winters, this happens.

02:05.185 --> 02:06.741
There's water down there.

02:07.258 --> 02:10.840
The hot springs inland find
their way out into the bay right

02:10.902 --> 02:12.522
under the road.

02:12.858 --> 02:14.642
Don't think about taking a dip though.

02:14.705 --> 02:18.974
It's still icy cold, and the water
will freeze the blood in your veins.

02:19.018 --> 02:21.388
Kill you stone dead in a minute.

02:21.418 --> 02:23.248
Man in your physical condition.

02:23.273 --> 02:25.714
I wasn't thinking about "taking a dip".

02:25.750 --> 02:27.459
Old and overweight.

02:28.683 --> 02:29.551
Ugh.

02:30.311 --> 02:32.093
What am I supposed to do about it?

02:33.800 --> 02:37.342
Governor Odegard used to call
Kim Hopperstad, he'd bring his

02:37.375 --> 02:39.222
digger out and fix it.

02:39.276 --> 02:40.545
Is that so?

02:41.130 --> 02:43.552
Do you know how many
murders I have on my plate?

02:43.599 --> 02:49.428
Four... Hindemith, Tavra, poor
Bianca, and now Tomak at the Blue Fox.

02:49.471 --> 02:52.346
Although, technically, I'd
consider Tavra a suicide.

02:52.348 --> 02:54.879
Right. Can we just leave this for now?

02:55.751 --> 02:57.294
Kim only takes cash.

02:58.889 --> 02:59.944
(TRUCK DOOR CLOSES)

03:15.689 --> 03:16.705
Find anything?

03:17.272 --> 03:19.625
Tomak had a lot of mobile phones.

03:20.182 --> 03:22.382
Get Petter Hansen to unlock them.

03:27.493 --> 03:28.943
Hello, Mrs. Odegard.

03:37.994 --> 03:40.482
_

03:41.160 --> 03:42.099
(SIGHS)

03:54.512 --> 03:55.305
Any idea who did this?

03:55.307 --> 03:57.787
I'm afraid I can't
discuss the investigation.

03:57.789 --> 03:58.556
(SHE SCOFFS)

03:58.595 --> 04:02.687
Of course. Do you have a moment?

04:02.689 --> 04:05.026
I need to speak to you
about something else.

04:05.080 --> 04:07.791
You didn't want to speak to me
about something else yesterday.

04:08.530 --> 04:11.200
Eric, please. It's important.

04:11.241 --> 04:12.534
How's your room here, by the way?

04:12.536 --> 04:15.610
It's a professional matter, I
have something to report to you.

04:15.612 --> 04:17.733
It's about Erling Munk.
I have some information...

04:17.735 --> 04:21.062
I'm sorry, Hildur, I have
a meeting with the governor.

04:26.572 --> 04:27.705
(SIGHS)

04:30.310 --> 04:32.202
He's under a lot of strain.

04:32.961 --> 04:34.378
Yes, I know.

04:34.677 --> 04:35.599
(THUD)

04:36.498 --> 04:37.719
Hey, Vince.

04:38.908 --> 04:40.759
- You okay? You sleep alright?
- (THUD)

04:40.761 --> 04:43.137
- Yeah. Great. Thank you.
- (THUD)

04:44.550 --> 04:45.244
(THUD)

04:45.259 --> 04:46.759
Back to work already?

04:46.822 --> 04:49.246
The samples we brought back from the
Tundra, the Reindeer, and the Bear.

04:49.301 --> 04:52.123
I... just love to get
started on the analyses.

04:52.326 --> 04:55.765
I'm sorry. I don't think
you're ready to go back to work.

04:56.479 --> 04:58.658
I think maybe you should get some help!

05:02.912 --> 05:03.996
Shut the door.

05:17.596 --> 05:21.077
Last night, Dan Anderssen broke
my patient out of the secure lab.

05:21.149 --> 05:22.215
What, the girl in the coma?

05:22.250 --> 05:24.062
We need to get her back immediately.

05:24.398 --> 05:28.834
Well, we have limited
resources and other priorities.

05:28.869 --> 05:32.025
- Not any more.
- Is she infectious or something?

05:32.060 --> 05:34.070
No, but we can say that if that helped.

05:34.123 --> 05:37.792
If it helped? Are you insane?

05:37.827 --> 05:41.992
This place is a powder keg
of well-armed drunks... who'll

05:42.027 --> 05:46.232
shut themselves in their
hovels and shoot on sight!

05:46.326 --> 05:47.935
We won't find anyone.

05:48.086 --> 05:50.782
My mandate from Schentel
Biotech says you do what I say in

05:50.824 --> 05:52.263
matters such as this.

05:52.473 --> 05:55.582
I need my patient back
now, and preferably alive.

05:55.617 --> 05:58.405
Then give me a story that won't
set this shit heap on fire.

05:58.440 --> 06:00.159
- (KNOCK AT THE DOOR)
- I mean it.

06:01.010 --> 06:02.005
Eric.

06:03.647 --> 06:04.530
Governor.

06:09.142 --> 06:09.999
Doctor.

06:11.213 --> 06:12.432
Sit down, Eric.

06:14.896 --> 06:21.015
Eric, I need you to direct
your resources to finding

06:21.050 --> 06:23.687
Dan Anderssen and Elena Ledesma.

06:26.487 --> 06:28.842
Governor, there's another
body in the morgue.

06:31.456 --> 06:34.781
I'm looking for someone who
has killed at least one person,

06:34.826 --> 06:36.232
maybe four.

06:37.566 --> 06:42.293
Sheriff, without the medication
keeping her alive, Elena will die.

06:42.363 --> 06:44.569
She doesn't know this and neither does Dan.

06:45.140 --> 06:47.740
We have to find them. Now.

06:50.727 --> 06:56.664
Eric... the dead can
wait for their vengeance.

06:58.186 --> 06:59.964
Our duty is to the living.

07:00.027 --> 07:01.365
What if someone else gets killed?

07:01.400 --> 07:03.554
Find the girl first, Sheriff.

07:03.946 --> 07:05.314
That's an order!

07:06.534 --> 07:08.054
(GASPS)

07:19.469 --> 07:20.404
Ah!

07:20.439 --> 07:21.180
(RETCHING)

07:21.229 --> 07:22.083
(CLATTERING)

07:22.122 --> 07:23.013
(RATTLING)

07:24.354 --> 07:26.549
(ETHEREAL MUSIC PLAYING)

07:26.923 --> 07:27.896
Help me!

07:29.757 --> 07:30.987
(VOMITS)

07:39.254 --> 07:42.526
Dan... are you okay?

07:44.383 --> 07:48.725
For a while there, I could
not remember anything.

07:49.722 --> 07:55.161
Oh. Everything feels like a dream.

07:55.336 --> 07:56.910
And not a good one.

07:58.325 --> 08:02.453
I remember... you were there, in the dark.

08:05.319 --> 08:06.925
You came to see me.

08:11.084 --> 08:13.403
Or did I dream that?

08:14.334 --> 08:15.330
No.

08:20.670 --> 08:21.992
I was there.

08:23.670 --> 08:26.477
I was so happy to hear your voice.

08:31.988 --> 08:33.655
With the woman.

08:34.568 --> 08:36.097
Dr. Khatri.

08:37.962 --> 08:39.106
Yeah.

08:42.534 --> 08:44.533
I called out to you, Dan.

08:46.411 --> 08:50.186
"Please, take me out of here. Please."

08:50.361 --> 08:56.894
I remember she was cutting me, and...
and I could feel the knife inside me...

08:58.191 --> 09:04.673
and all I could do was scream in the dark.

09:05.741 --> 09:08.983
"Stop it. Stop it, please".

09:09.045 --> 09:13.835
She didn't. She couldn't hear me.

09:14.377 --> 09:18.881
Maybe she could. Maybe she knew.

09:20.264 --> 09:23.565
Well, that's... inhuman.

09:25.174 --> 09:27.058
It's a whole new world.

09:41.174 --> 09:43.094
(SHE WHEEZES)

10:14.678 --> 10:16.518
(CAR STARTS)

10:26.690 --> 10:29.170
(HE BREATHES SHAKILY)

10:29.205 --> 10:30.502
(CRYING)

10:44.199 --> 10:47.932
I am... I am sorry.

10:49.309 --> 10:55.089
Forgive me. Forgive me. I had to do it.

10:57.188 --> 11:02.092
This box was smuggled out of
the Russian town of Vukobejina a

11:02.161 --> 11:11.094
few days ago. It's got film, got
medical records, and army reports.

11:15.653 --> 11:17.079
I'll get the lights.

11:23.015 --> 11:27.397
The film relates to the
events of 1942 in the summer,

11:27.432 --> 11:31.479
it was the warmest summer in
the Arctic since records began.

11:32.212 --> 11:35.279
There was a team of Russian
scientists, who were from a

11:35.314 --> 11:39.729
weather station over on the east coast,
they reported a plague of wasps...

11:40.631 --> 11:43.119
and then a massacre.

11:49.449 --> 11:53.164
This is a reindeer
herders camp. A Sami camp.

11:55.019 --> 12:00.947
Everyone dead. They sent in the
Red Army who found one survivor.

12:03.272 --> 12:06.155
This man... this man is infected.

12:06.204 --> 12:09.840
There's parasitic wasp
inside him, just like here.

12:10.832 --> 12:14.489
The Sami, they chained
him up and left him to die.

12:14.581 --> 12:15.756
But he didn't die.

12:15.811 --> 12:19.427
He survived on his own
for weeks without food

12:19.462 --> 12:21.796
and with very little water.

12:22.073 --> 12:25.070
And he beat the wasp.

12:25.105 --> 12:26.697
But when they took the chains off of him,

12:26.745 --> 12:28.762
he killed sixteen people.

12:30.102 --> 12:33.430
And they had to take him down with
four bullets, it took to take him down.

12:35.607 --> 12:37.821
The doctors started opening him up.

12:37.883 --> 12:38.860
And...

12:39.526 --> 12:41.486
he should be dead... look at him!

12:45.266 --> 12:53.860
The notes speak of "unprecedented
organ and tissue regeneration".

12:56.363 --> 12:58.209
Where are the medical files?

12:58.210 --> 13:01.330
They're all right here.
They're all in Russian.

13:01.421 --> 13:02.623
You translated them?

13:02.681 --> 13:05.335
No... but she did.

13:05.370 --> 13:06.720
This is Yeva.

13:06.836 --> 13:09.857
Her uncle is the mayor of
Vukobejina. He's my friend.

13:09.921 --> 13:11.488
He sent all this.

13:11.545 --> 13:12.795
(PROJECTOR SHUTS OFF)

13:19.274 --> 13:23.899
I'm sorry, but has anyone considered
the possibility that this is a hoax?

13:24.194 --> 13:28.494
The film is old. The
files... everything's old!

13:28.575 --> 13:29.798
Tissue regeneration...

13:29.833 --> 13:32.911
It's, it's, it's quiet common in nature.

13:32.946 --> 13:36.362
That's right, that's right, I've
read about it, and they can make

13:36.397 --> 13:39.586
new limbs, even eyes.

13:44.846 --> 13:46.950
This is not a hoax.

13:47.240 --> 13:50.121
Is what happened here in
Fortitude, is that a hoax?

13:50.179 --> 13:55.544
This is REAL. THIS... IS REAL.
It happened, seventy years ago.

13:55.596 --> 13:57.791
Right on the other side of this island.

13:57.826 --> 14:01.955
Same wasp, same shit that we've had here.

14:02.862 --> 14:07.802
Only this time... something
good came out of this.

14:09.399 --> 14:14.415
Something different,
something fucking miraculous.

14:14.943 --> 14:16.926
Something that can heal us.

14:42.589 --> 14:45.241
You have to serve yourself around here now.

14:46.604 --> 14:49.529
I can't imagine how hard this is for you.

14:52.390 --> 14:54.248
What else am I gonna do?

15:00.944 --> 15:02.465
(GRUNTS)

15:06.922 --> 15:11.780
The Russians set up some
sort of temporary medical lab

15:11.827 --> 15:14.762
near that weather
station back in forty two.

15:15.353 --> 15:18.469
Yeva says that weather
station is still there.

15:18.504 --> 15:19.847
She knows where to find it.

15:19.893 --> 15:25.249
If I can just find that lab,
if I could fight something...

15:25.284 --> 15:27.047
Did you hear those scientists?

15:28.047 --> 15:31.852
They made me feel like I was bullshit,
they're weren't even listening.

15:31.935 --> 15:37.436
Khatri was listening. For her,
the film was not such a surprise.

15:39.040 --> 15:40.139
How do you mean?

15:40.259 --> 15:43.706
I don't know. There's
something here, something big,

15:43.741 --> 15:45.639
something connected.

15:46.973 --> 15:50.063
But I can't see it yet, only parts of it.

15:51.485 --> 15:53.076
Munk's part of it.

15:53.845 --> 15:59.164
Getting rid of me, promoting Eric...
it's part of a plan, or a pattern.

16:00.125 --> 16:03.348
The killings too, they're
not random as Eric thinks.

16:04.237 --> 16:05.865
But Munk is the key.

16:06.030 --> 16:07.405
(KNOCKS ON DOOR)

16:11.765 --> 16:15.630
Groceries. Clothes.

16:28.925 --> 16:31.065
You have to come back to FARC with me.

16:32.044 --> 16:35.063
- No!
- We're giving them to everyone in town.

16:36.325 --> 16:40.484
Our friend Elena is sick. Without
her medication she will die.

16:40.578 --> 16:42.137
Please help us find her now.

16:42.183 --> 16:46.438
If you see her or Dan Anderssen,
call Eric, Ingrid or Petra.

16:46.496 --> 16:47.978
It's a lie.

16:48.071 --> 16:49.564
What is?

16:49.621 --> 16:54.040
It's not true. She's not sick.
She doesn't need medication.

16:54.095 --> 16:55.203
She's not going to die.

16:55.246 --> 17:00.981
Petra. Petra, he's
right. I'm fine here, now.

17:01.965 --> 17:05.498
Elena wasn't a patient, she was a lab rat.

17:05.568 --> 17:08.648
The machines weren't keeping her
alive, they were keeping her asleep.

17:09.127 --> 17:14.310
I'm not... going back
there. I'm, I'm not. I won't.

17:14.345 --> 17:15.037
I won't.

17:15.071 --> 17:19.770
Okay. Okay. You can stay here. For now.

17:19.805 --> 17:23.844
But you're coming with me, Dan.
You have to tell Eric what you said.

17:23.884 --> 17:26.204
No, I don't. He can't cope as it is.

17:28.509 --> 17:32.959
Dan Anderssen, I have orders to arrest
you and bring you in for questioning.

17:45.486 --> 17:47.148
You don't need the gun, Petra.

17:59.195 --> 18:00.534
You're not leaving.

18:02.075 --> 18:03.880
You'll bleed again.

18:03.915 --> 18:06.884
He's getting stronger, the demon.

18:06.941 --> 18:09.456
So little time left. It has to be stopped.

18:09.491 --> 18:11.665
The police are looking for you.

18:11.712 --> 18:12.571
(HE GRUNTS)

18:12.627 --> 18:18.426
They think you killed Tavra and
that geologist. Vladek, did you?

18:20.061 --> 18:22.840
I am not your problem.

18:23.086 --> 18:24.055
(SIGHS HEAVILY)

18:29.212 --> 18:33.253
Tavra killed himself because he had to.

18:34.635 --> 18:38.395
I killed the geologist because
he couldn't kill himself.

18:44.275 --> 18:45.761
Is that true?

18:46.787 --> 18:48.922
It is if you believe me.

18:50.835 --> 18:54.354
If you have faith in me.

18:54.410 --> 18:56.330
Do you, Freya?

18:59.152 --> 19:00.595
I don't know.

19:05.692 --> 19:07.282
- Your money.
- What?

19:07.345 --> 19:09.533
You wanted some cash from the bank.

19:09.604 --> 19:12.148
For Kim Hopperstad to fix the hole.

19:12.183 --> 19:14.499
But you couldn't be
bothered going yourself.

19:14.534 --> 19:16.189
Kim'll see you there at four.

19:16.240 --> 19:17.221
Why can't you go?

19:17.256 --> 19:21.159
It's dangerous. Road's full of holes.

19:21.880 --> 19:24.513
Perhaps I should find
myself a younger assistant.

19:24.571 --> 19:26.225
I'm not dead, you know.

19:26.986 --> 19:28.255
It won't be long.

19:28.320 --> 19:30.291
Not fucking deaf either.

19:31.652 --> 19:35.172
For God's sake, Ingrid!
Elena cannot just disappear.

19:38.236 --> 19:39.309
Keep looking.

19:41.108 --> 19:43.014
Look what I found by the harbour.

19:44.195 --> 19:45.503
Hello, Eric.

19:51.755 --> 19:52.617
Dan.

19:54.156 --> 19:57.874
I'm trying to find a man who
has killed a lot of people here.

19:58.857 --> 20:03.594
But I can't do that until
I know Elena is safe.

20:03.595 --> 20:07.177
You know where she is. Help me.

20:11.075 --> 20:12.517
Help her.

20:22.795 --> 20:27.634
Dan, don't make me lock you up.

20:27.703 --> 20:29.180
What are the charges?

20:29.231 --> 20:30.914
You broke into Khatri's house.

20:30.915 --> 20:32.035
To cook her a three course meal.

20:32.101 --> 20:33.560
It was a fucking home invasion!

20:33.595 --> 20:34.837
I stacked the dishwasher.

20:34.875 --> 20:37.750
You put a flare gun in her face.

20:38.801 --> 20:39.851
It wasn't loaded.

20:39.894 --> 20:41.975
Dan, please.

20:47.962 --> 20:51.617
Dr. Khatri's pressing
charges... threatening behaviour,

20:51.679 --> 20:55.153
breaking and entering,
assault with a deadly weapon.

20:55.188 --> 20:59.518
You'll be taken to Oslo for
a trial. Put him in a cell.

21:04.155 --> 21:06.035
I'm entitled to a phone call.

21:32.155 --> 21:33.795
(ELECTRICITY CRACKLES)

21:54.996 --> 21:57.234
Why didn't you tell Eric what you told me?

21:57.881 --> 21:58.959
Hmm.

21:59.875 --> 22:01.563
I didn't think he'd listen.

22:03.284 --> 22:04.389
I know!

22:06.572 --> 22:12.892
I told him... I think the killer's
a Shaman, Dan... but he won't listen.

22:14.835 --> 22:16.526
He's out of his depth.

22:18.740 --> 22:20.100
Go on.

22:22.813 --> 22:27.178
There's a legend among the people
here... that every few generations

22:27.213 --> 22:31.533
the Gods send down a plague to
remind everyone of their power.

22:32.190 --> 22:36.727
And after the plague, a,
a sort of demon rises up.

22:36.795 --> 22:42.500
The chosen one... and he can only
be defeated by a powerful magic,

22:42.555 --> 22:45.332
and for that, the Shaman
needs certain body parts.

22:45.899 --> 22:50.327
And that's what I think is
happening here: the husky, the heads,

22:50.362 --> 22:51.166
the heart...

22:51.236 --> 22:56.759
Someone is collecting body parts because
they think there is a monster here.

22:59.091 --> 23:00.368
A monster?

23:03.840 --> 23:06.172
It's only superstition, of course.

23:08.195 --> 23:12.737
But if we can understand
his way of thinking, then...

23:12.788 --> 23:15.128
We can predict his moves.

23:16.315 --> 23:17.376
That's it!

23:29.702 --> 23:34.554
Against my advice, Dr. Surinder Khatri
has agreed to speak to you in private.

23:46.628 --> 23:50.640
If you drop the charges,
I'll keep my mouth shut.

23:51.716 --> 23:53.036
How does that sound?

23:59.148 --> 24:02.614
Hey. Can I get a hand putting
the Ski-Doos on the trailer?

24:05.861 --> 24:08.418
- Did I interrupt something here?
- No.

24:11.925 --> 24:13.797
Gotta admit, I had my doubts about her.

24:13.855 --> 24:17.746
But after getting to know her for
a few days, she's pretty great.

24:17.802 --> 24:19.441
She's not my girlfriend.

24:20.500 --> 24:21.719
Just saying.

24:22.246 --> 24:23.966
Don't embarrass me. Okay?

24:24.564 --> 24:29.274
Hey, I told your mother
we're going hunting. Okay?

24:29.355 --> 24:30.144
Alright.

24:32.323 --> 24:34.015
Did you eat something?

24:34.627 --> 24:36.369
We're wasting daylight.

24:44.381 --> 24:47.575
Don't you be doing anything
stupid while I'm gone.

24:49.483 --> 24:52.273
You try not to shoot Rune!

24:52.612 --> 24:53.620
(HE CHUCKLES)

25:06.331 --> 25:07.811
(THEY WHOOP AND SHOUT)

25:14.027 --> 25:14.949
(ELEVATOR BELL DINGS)

25:17.241 --> 25:18.960
I just saw this.

25:18.995 --> 25:20.400
I wanted to ask you, what happened?

25:20.435 --> 25:22.160
She came out of the coma
yesterday, quite suddenly.

25:22.195 --> 25:22.994
No brain damage?

25:23.035 --> 25:25.298
She was dirsorientated and violent.
I had no time to examine her.

25:25.372 --> 25:27.331
But, wasn't she
effectively on life-support?

25:27.395 --> 25:29.674
It's a miracle, Doctor Yelburton.

25:29.675 --> 25:31.057
Why did she attack you?

25:31.109 --> 25:32.249
- Be happy.
- (DOOR OPENS)

25:33.164 --> 25:34.195
(DOOR CLOSES)

25:38.676 --> 25:40.223
What did you do to Khatri?

25:40.550 --> 25:41.950
Did you threaten her?

25:44.387 --> 25:46.154
I don't know you anymore.

25:47.932 --> 25:49.623
- Dan!
- Hildur.

25:49.866 --> 25:51.746
I've been worried about you.

26:06.172 --> 26:07.867
Hildur, come inside. Please.

26:10.631 --> 26:12.876
Petter, could you give us a moment?

26:18.411 --> 26:19.737
Petter, get out of here!

26:26.404 --> 26:29.362
I'm sorry about this
morning. My timing was bad.

26:29.397 --> 26:30.821
No, I'm sorry.

26:31.721 --> 26:37.439
Just got so much to deal with, you know...

26:37.499 --> 26:40.539
I know... I know.

26:43.915 --> 26:48.875
But... most of all, err...

26:52.995 --> 26:55.395
most of all, I'm, I'm upset.

27:00.901 --> 27:05.948
I'm upset because you
don't love me any more.

27:12.604 --> 27:15.162
(EXHALES) I don't know. I...

27:16.899 --> 27:19.058
I think I'm unhappy.

27:19.155 --> 27:21.481
I, I have been for quite a while.

27:21.562 --> 27:24.123
And I don't really know why.

27:30.164 --> 27:32.135
Well, I can wait if...

27:33.601 --> 27:35.342
If that's what it takes.

27:35.829 --> 27:36.681
(SCOFFS)

27:37.403 --> 27:38.340
Thank you.

27:42.748 --> 27:44.347
You wanted to talk to me.

27:44.395 --> 27:49.694
Yes. Eric, it's important.

27:51.475 --> 27:54.656
Erling Munk is corrupt.

27:55.409 --> 27:59.322
He's being paid by a third party
to control events in Fortitude

27:59.381 --> 28:00.725
and report back.

28:01.698 --> 28:05.767
He contacts them on a separate
mobile phone he keeps in his room.

28:06.195 --> 28:10.231
Yesterday, I flew down to Oslo,
to see his former secretary.

28:10.289 --> 28:12.196
She's also his mistress.

28:12.282 --> 28:16.030
She told me he has a second
property, something he could

28:16.065 --> 28:18.290
never afford on a government salary.

28:18.325 --> 28:21.834
He keeps a sports car there in a garage.

28:21.835 --> 28:24.373
Everything in a different
name, some relative of his.

28:24.408 --> 28:29.380
I, I have a... A photo of
Munk in the car at the house.

28:30.044 --> 28:32.523
The local police will easily find it.

28:32.599 --> 28:36.164
In the meantime, we need a
warrant to access his bank records

28:36.199 --> 28:38.693
- and seize his phones.
- Jesus Christ!

28:38.728 --> 28:42.018
I know! He always seemed so upright!

28:42.387 --> 28:46.286
You just lost your job, okay?

28:47.028 --> 28:48.899
But your life is not over.

28:50.860 --> 28:56.592
People have real problems. Death. Loss.

28:57.315 --> 29:04.418
I don't know, maybe you
need counseling or something.

29:05.292 --> 29:07.747
You think I'm making this up?

29:07.782 --> 29:11.999
I heard him on the phone, I have
emails that he wrote, they prove...

29:12.046 --> 29:13.197
- they prove that...
- What?

29:13.278 --> 29:17.950
What? Conspiracy
theory... bullshit! Christ!

29:19.507 --> 29:20.795
I have work to do.

29:27.451 --> 29:28.889
(BREATHING ANGRILY)

29:34.063 --> 29:34.668
(THUD)

29:34.718 --> 29:35.843
- Ah!
- (MUG SHATTERS)

29:39.162 --> 29:40.310
(GRUNTING)

29:45.777 --> 29:46.972
- (PANTING)
- (HE BREATHES DEEPLY)

30:00.660 --> 30:02.900
(HEAVY BREATHING)

30:03.627 --> 30:05.027
Why can't you love me?

30:33.915 --> 30:35.353
(BREATHING SHAKILY)

31:20.202 --> 31:21.333
Elena.

31:25.405 --> 31:26.476
Elena?

31:27.963 --> 31:29.025
Elena?

31:31.475 --> 31:32.307
Elena?

31:32.650 --> 31:33.448
ELENA?

31:33.483 --> 31:36.847
(BREATHES DEEPLY) What? What is it?

31:38.822 --> 31:40.421
I thought you were dead.

31:40.456 --> 31:41.411
No.

31:44.277 --> 31:45.410
(SHE GRUNTS)

31:49.124 --> 31:50.937
I wanna go back.

31:53.376 --> 31:55.970
(BREATHES DEEPLY) I wanna leave.

31:56.045 --> 32:00.164
It's not safe yet. You
can't trust anyone here.

32:00.237 --> 32:02.202
Can I trust you, Dan?

32:03.201 --> 32:05.290
I'm the only one you can trust.

32:06.665 --> 32:11.184
Didn't you try to kill me?
Or did I dream that too?

32:11.219 --> 32:12.199
No.

32:15.985 --> 32:18.886
I didn't want you to
end up like the others.

32:21.166 --> 32:23.114
How did they end up?

32:24.275 --> 32:28.370
They got eaten alive from the inside
by larvae from a prehistoric wasp.

32:31.745 --> 32:32.981
A what?

32:34.545 --> 32:36.011
Are you making fun of me?

32:36.074 --> 32:39.794
No. That's what happened.

32:41.152 --> 32:43.181
That's what happened to people here.

32:44.385 --> 32:46.100
And it happened to me too.

32:47.105 --> 32:51.915
After I thought I'd killed
you, I had a couple of drinks.

32:52.514 --> 32:55.354
A few days later, I woke up here.

32:56.185 --> 32:59.880
And by then, the voices were inside me.

33:00.410 --> 33:05.843
I could hear them talking to me,
whispering to me, telling me what to do.

33:08.420 --> 33:09.830
The voices.

33:10.625 --> 33:12.196
And I knew I'd do it.

33:16.465 --> 33:18.975
Did you chain yourself up?

33:19.328 --> 33:23.624
Just me and the voices
and anything I could drink.

33:23.659 --> 33:26.249
Even Henry's reindeer juice.

33:26.361 --> 33:29.013
Oh, I knew I'd die... eventually.

33:31.545 --> 33:35.936
Where are they now, Dan... The Voices?

33:39.945 --> 33:41.505
That's a good question.

33:51.035 --> 33:52.194
Hildur!

33:52.239 --> 33:54.854
Hello, Ralfi. Is Munk in?

33:54.889 --> 33:56.077
I need to see him.

33:56.116 --> 33:58.516
No. Gone for the day.

33:58.995 --> 34:02.434
Really? Where?

34:02.435 --> 34:06.293
Out to the old cement factory.
The road's shite again.

34:06.402 --> 34:09.460
He's meeting Kim Hopperstad there at four.

34:09.630 --> 34:11.467
(MUSIC PLAYING IN THE CAR)

34:34.518 --> 34:35.585
(CELL PHONE BEEPS)

34:49.529 --> 34:50.839
(HE TURNS OFF THE MUSIC) Hildur.

34:52.679 --> 34:54.038
What are you doing out here?

34:54.120 --> 34:56.000
I came to talk to you, Erling.

34:57.755 --> 35:00.222
I'm here to see the digger man.

35:00.714 --> 35:02.886
- Kim Hopperstad?
- Hmm.

35:06.443 --> 35:14.584
Increasingly, I find my life has
the quality of a... bad dream.

35:16.077 --> 35:18.287
- I'm very sorry, Erling.
- (SCOFFS)

35:19.621 --> 35:25.131
I've known you twenty years,
and I can't imagine what sort of

35:25.166 --> 35:27.748
mess you got yourself into to end up here.

35:27.783 --> 35:28.909
(CHUCKLES SARCASTICALLY)

35:31.212 --> 35:33.125
I'm not quite with you, Hildur.

35:33.644 --> 35:36.701
I know, Erling. I know everything.

35:36.780 --> 35:38.883
Everything that matters anyway.

35:39.484 --> 35:44.954
I saw the emails on your laptop,
gently engineering my removal.

35:44.998 --> 35:48.170
And the others, quietly taking my place.

35:49.347 --> 35:52.107
It was brilliantly done, of course.

35:52.635 --> 35:56.448
They'd have seen it as a selfless
demotion for the good of the team.

35:57.245 --> 35:59.354
Instead of what it was:

35:59.355 --> 36:00.335
Obeying orders.

36:00.370 --> 36:02.399
I don't know what you're talking about.

36:03.180 --> 36:07.685
I was hiding in your room that
night, the night of the bar fight.

36:08.411 --> 36:11.074
Michael Lennox was supposed
to keep you down there.

36:11.642 --> 36:17.106
I went through your emails, and when
you came back, I heard you on the phone.

36:17.702 --> 36:20.561
You were reporting back about
the progress of the murder

36:20.597 --> 36:25.547
investigations, about what I
was doing, and about how Eric was

36:25.612 --> 36:28.571
an idiot, and that's
why you made him Sheriff.

36:28.606 --> 36:32.919
"It's all under control," you
said. "But I want more money."

36:35.749 --> 36:36.856
(GRUNTS)

36:41.896 --> 36:43.496
(VOMITS)

36:46.444 --> 36:49.662
Marika told me about your second
house in Oslo... the one in

36:49.697 --> 36:53.411
your uncle's name, and
the car you keep out there.

36:55.327 --> 36:59.883
I'm very sorry, Erling.
How did it all start?

37:00.525 --> 37:03.619
It's not too late, you
know. I can help you.

37:03.692 --> 37:05.204
You can help me.

37:08.355 --> 37:09.826
I'm not going to the Police.

37:09.889 --> 37:12.373
I don't care about the
money, or who you work for.

37:12.408 --> 37:14.394
I care about Fortitude.

37:15.254 --> 37:19.828
So here's my deal: you resign
the governor's job, you find some

37:19.870 --> 37:22.931
excuse, and you go home to Oslo.

37:23.010 --> 37:28.839
In return, I forget
everything, this all goes away.

37:28.874 --> 37:30.471
- Liar!
- (SHE GRUNTS)

37:31.263 --> 37:34.013
(SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYS)

37:39.275 --> 37:41.544
Erling! (SHE GASPS)

37:48.669 --> 37:50.372
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

37:51.418 --> 37:52.568
Help me.

37:56.275 --> 37:57.435
Give me your hand.

38:00.745 --> 38:01.561
(SHE GRUNTS)

38:01.596 --> 38:02.999
- I can't!
- Take my hand.

38:03.073 --> 38:04.307
I can't...

38:06.976 --> 38:08.155
Give me your hand.

38:10.581 --> 38:11.550
(GASPS)

38:19.491 --> 38:21.527
Pull me up... quick!

38:23.635 --> 38:24.736
Quick!

38:28.294 --> 38:29.364
Erling!

38:29.624 --> 38:35.184
It starts off small, and then you're
in, and they won't let go of you.

38:38.233 --> 38:39.553
I'm trapped, Hildur.

38:40.967 --> 38:41.952
Ah!

38:43.881 --> 38:48.557
I'm in up to my head. Like you said.

38:48.664 --> 38:53.173
No. Erling, we can, we can
work it out, we... Please.

38:53.963 --> 38:57.115
Please. Please.

38:59.123 --> 39:00.619
Forgive me, Hildur...

39:00.654 --> 39:02.365
(GASPING)

39:03.223 --> 39:04.234
but I can't.

39:04.305 --> 39:05.920
No! (GASPS)

39:05.973 --> 39:07.196
I can't do it.

39:07.635 --> 39:08.484
No.

39:11.115 --> 39:14.072
No. Erling! ARGH!

39:23.466 --> 39:26.826
(BURSTS OF STATIC)

39:45.263 --> 39:46.247
(GRUNTS)

39:49.606 --> 39:51.446
(WHIMPERING)

40:08.088 --> 40:09.347
- (PHONE RINGS)
- (GASPS)

40:26.667 --> 40:28.406
- (ENGINE FAILS TO START)
- (GRUNTS)

40:28.484 --> 40:29.481
Fuck.

40:29.516 --> 40:30.696
(ENGINE REVS)

40:37.168 --> 40:39.394
Come on... OH, FUCK!

41:02.420 --> 41:03.389
(GRUNTS)

41:06.467 --> 41:07.365
(GRUNTS)

41:14.016 --> 41:16.775
(HE PANTS)

41:44.384 --> 41:45.371
(COIN RATTLES)

41:45.411 --> 41:46.935
(CHATTER AND LAUGHTER IN BACKGROUND)

41:48.256 --> 41:50.919
(Dusty Springfield's "Take Another
Little Piece of My Heart" plays)

41:57.856 --> 42:03.612
Someone's hiding them. The
Shaman... and Elena. Both of them.

42:04.624 --> 42:06.540
Probably someone in here.

42:09.225 --> 42:10.584
I'm an alcoholic.

42:43.256 --> 42:44.498
(RUNE LAUGHS)

43:16.086 --> 43:18.068
(PHONE RINGS)

43:30.941 --> 43:34.101
(EVERYONE SINGS)

44:19.078 --> 44:20.758
(HE CRIES)

44:23.470 --> 44:26.230
(HE LAUGHS)

44:55.163 --> 44:56.287
_

44:56.360 --> 44:57.355
- (BOTH GRUNTING)
- Ugh!

45:02.184 --> 45:03.978
Get fucking finding!

